kpi_info.title: rrc_co_re_term_cu
kpi_info.use: A number of establishment requests for terminating call; the cause unknown. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC_CONNECTION_REQUEST message (with CAUSE Terminating - cause unknown) from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_co_re_orig_sub_traf
kpi_info.use: A number of establishment requests for an originating subscribed traffic call. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC_CONNECTION_REQUEST message (with CAUSE Originating subscribed traffic call) from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_req_call_re_estab
kpi_info.use: A number of requests for call re-establishments. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC_CONNECTION_REQUEST message (with CAUSE Call re-establishments) from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_req_fail
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection request failures. When the message is tried to be decoded and the data is corrupted, the message cannot be interpreted (Unable to solve ASN.1 coding or the reason unknown). UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity is unable to solve the RRC connection request.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_reject
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC Connection Request Reject messages. When the RRC signalling entity acknowledges the rejection to the UE. The reason for the rejection can be: - Internal reason - BTS reason - Transmission reason - AC reason. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RRC_CONNECTION_REJECT message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_setup
kpi_info.use: The number or RRC:RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages sent by the RNC. This counter includes also repeated sendings of the message due to RNC internal timer expiry or due to a new RRC CONNECTION REQUEST from the UE. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC: RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_setup_compl_sent
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE messages received. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_rel
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection releases. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC_CONNECTION_RELEASE message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_1_att_cn_orig
kpi_info.use: The number of CN originated paging type 1 attempts. Indicates the number of CN originated paging attempts to UEs in idle, Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. UPDATED: When the RNC L2 entity has successfully scheduled PAGING TYPE 1 message for sending to the BTS and the paging procedure is triggered by the RANAP: PAGING message received from CN. Paging messages dropped due to overload are not included.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_1_att_rnc_orig
kpi_info.use: The number of RNC originated paging type 1 attempts. Indicates the number of RNC originated paging attempts to UEs in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. UPDATED:When the RNC L2 entity has successfully scheduled PAGING TYPE 1 message for sending to the BTS and the paging procedure is triggered by the RNC (e.g. after DL data received from PS-CN). Paging messages dropped due to overload are not included.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_2_att
kpi_info.use: A number of paging type 2 attempts. Indicates the number of (CN originated) paging attempts to mobiles in DCH or RACH/FACH substate. UPDATED:When the RNC sends a PAGING_TYPE_2 message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rb_setup
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer setups. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RADIO_BEARER_SETUP message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rb_setup_complete
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer setups completed. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RADIO_BEARER_SETUP_COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rb_reconf
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer reconfigurations. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RADIO_BEARER_RECONFIGURATION message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rb_reconf_complete
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer reconfigurations completed. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RADIO_BEARER_RECONFIGURATION_COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: tran_ch_reconf
kpi_info.use: "A number of transport channel reconfigurations. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity sends a TRANPORT_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION message to the UE."

kpi_info.title: tran_ch_reconf_comp
kpi_info.use: A number of transport channel reconfigurations completed. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a TRANSPORT_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION_COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_due_cell_res
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to a cell reselection. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Cell reselection'.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_per_update
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to periodic update. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Periodic update'.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_data_transm
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to UL data transmission. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'UL data transmission'.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_paging_resp
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to a paging response. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Paging response'.

kpi_info.title: cell_upd_att_re_ent_s_area
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to a re-entered service area. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Re-entered service area'.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_r_link_fail
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to a radio link failure. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Radio link failure'.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_rlc_err
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to an RLC unrecoverable error. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'RLC unrecoverable error'.

kpi_info.title: ura_update_att_change_of_ura
kpi_info.use: A number of URA update attempts due to a change of URA. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a URA_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Change of URA'.

kpi_info.title: ura_update_att_per_update
kpi_info.use: A number of URA update attempts due to periodic update. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a URA_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Periodic update'.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_mode_left_cell
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connected mode UEs that have moved to another cell. If an UE in CELL_DCH, CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH substate moves from the cell through SHO, HHO or CELL/URA update procedure. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity notices that the UE has moved to another cell.

kpi_info.title: cap_req_ul
kpi_info.use: "The number of uplink capacity requests received from the UE. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT message with trafficVolumeEventResults IE from the UE."

kpi_info.title: cell_dch_state_to_cell_fach
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_DCH state to CELL_FACH state. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE message and the dedicated channel release is triggered by a state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_to_cell_dch
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_DCH state. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC:RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message and the dedicated channel allocation is triggered by a state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_cell_pch_ina
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_PCH state after inactivity is detected. This counter is triggered when inactivity is detected in CELL_FACH. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC:PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE as a response to a state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_cell_pch_upd
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_PCH state after Cell Update attempt. This counter is triggered: - When UE has moved temporarily to CELL_FACH due to cell change, re-entered service area or periodic cell update and after that returns to CELL_PCH state. - The counter shows also CELL_FACH state UEs moved directly to URA_PCH state (cell change frequency causes direct state change to URA_PCH) UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity switches the UE back to the CELL_PCH state by sending an RRC:CELL_UPDATE_CONFIRM message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_to_ura_pch
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from CELL_FACH to URA_PCH state. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE.

kpi_info.title: mea_cap_req_for_dl
kpi_info.use: "The number of downlink capacity requests sent by RNC MAC-C to the RRC signalling entity, triggering state a transition attempt to CELL-DCH state. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives a downlink capacity request from MAC-C."

kpi_info.title: conn_cell_pch_due_ms_is_lost
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection releases in CELL_PCH state due to a reason 'MS is lost'. If the RNC cannot obtain any cell update message as a response to repeated paging to the MS. If the timer which supervises periodical CELL update expires and MS has not made a periodical update before that. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity releases the RRC connection due to the reason 'MS is lost'.

kpi_info.title: rrc_con_rel_update_conf_fail
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to cell or URA update confirmation failure. UPDATED: When the RNC cannot send the RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM to the UE, e.g. due to DMCU resource shortage, and therefore the RNC releases the RRC connection by sending RRC: RRC CONNECTION RELEASE to the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_con_rel_sig_con_re_est
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to the reason 'Directed signalling connection re-establishment'. This occurs when a UE in CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH or URA_PCH connected mode starts a CELL UPDATE/URA UPDATE procedure to a cell belonging to another RNC (than the SRNC) and relocation is not possible. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC_CONNECTION_RELEASE message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: ini_dir_tran
kpi_info.use: Number of Initial Direct Transfer messages UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a INITIAL_DIRECT_TRANSFER message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: sec_mod_contrl
kpi_info.use: Number of security mode control messages. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a SECURITY_MODE_CONTROL message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: sec_mod_contrl_comp
kpi_info.use: Number of security mode control complete messages. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a SECURITY_MODE_CONTROL_COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: sig_conn_rel
kpi_info.use: Number of signalling connection release messages. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a SIGNALLING_CONNECTION_RELEASE message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: sig_conn_rel_ind
kpi_info.use: Number of signalling connection release indication messages. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a SIGNALLING_CONNECTION_RELEASE_REQUEST message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: phy_ch_reconf
kpi_info.use: Number of physical channel reconfigurations. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a PHYSICAL_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: phy_ch_reconf_comp
kpi_info.use: Number of physical channel reconfigurations complete. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a PHYSICAL_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION_COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: inter_rat_ho_utran
kpi_info.use: Number of started Inter-RAT Hos for Packet Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC:CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: inter_rat_ho_utran_fail
kpi_info.use: Number of failed Inter-RAT HOs for Packet Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC: CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: ho_utran_com
kpi_info.use: Number of sent HO from UTRAN Commands for Circuit Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RRC: HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: ho_utran_com_fail
kpi_info.use: Number of received HO from UTRAN Command Failures for Circuit Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC: HANDOVER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: rrc_ho_utran_comp
kpi_info.use: Number of received RRC handover to UTRAN complete messages for Circuit Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a R RC:HANDOVER TO UTRAN COMPLETE message from the UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_MODE_LEFT_CELL_UPD
kpi_info.use: Number of RRC connected mode UEs that have moved to another cell through either CELL_UPDATE or URA_UPDATE procedure. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity notices that the UE has moved to another cell.

kpi_info.title: RB_RELEASE
kpi_info.use: Number of Radio Bearer Release messages sent. UPDATED:When RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE message is sent to UE.

kpi_info.title: RB_RELEASE_COMPLETE
kpi_info.use: Number of Radio Bearer Release complete messages received. UPDATED:When RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE message is received from UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_RMCU_OVERLOAD
kpi_info.use: Number of RRC Connection Request rejects due to RRMU overload (RNTI cannot be allocated). UPDATED:When RNTI cannot be allocated due to RRMU overload.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_DIR_SETUP
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Reject messages sent to the UE with RRC connection setup redirection information. In this case, the RRC connection request is rejected but the information of the other cell carrier is given where the UE should make a new connection request. The target cell can also be in the GSM network. UPDATED:When an RRC Connection Reject message is sent with redirection information.

kpi_info.title: DCH_TO_FACH_PS_INTERRUPT_TIM
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from CELL DCH to CELL FACH due to PS interruption timer. If PS Interruption Timer expires and there is another capacity request for the CELL that is under the same BTS, the packet scheduler of the RNC releases the dedicated transport channel and the related radio links. The UE is moved to Cell_FACH state unless it has other user plane dedicated transport channels allocated. UPDATED:When the UE is moved from Cell_DCH to Cell_FACH state due to PS Interruption Timer.

kpi_info.title: PHY_CH_RECONF_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of all the physical channel reconfiguration failures. UPDATED:When the RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: PHY_CH_RECONF_FAIL_UNS_CONF
kpi_info.use: The number of physical channel reconfiguration failures due to unsupported configuration. UPDATED:When the RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message with the cause "configuration unsupported" is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: RB_RECONF_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of all the radio bearer reconfiguration failures. UPDATED:When the RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: RB_RECONF_FAIL_UNS_CONF
kpi_info.use: The number of radio bearer reconfiguration failures due to unsupported configuration. UPDATED:When the RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message with the cause "configuration unsupported" is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: RB_SETUP_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of all the radio bearer setup failures. UPDATED:When the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE message is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: RB_SETUP_FAIL_UNS_CONF
kpi_info.use: The number of radio bearer setup failures due to unsupported configuration. UPDATED:When the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE message with the cause "configuration unsupported" is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: SPARE_1_RRC
kpi_info.use: Spare counter 1 for future use. UPDATED:Never.

kpi_info.title: SPARE_2_RRC
kpi_info.use: Spare counter 2 for future use. UPDATED:Never.

kpi_info.title: SPARE_3_RRC
kpi_info.use: Spare counter 3 for future use. UPDATED:Never.

kpi_info.title: TFC_CTRL_FOR_TFO
kpi_info.use: The number of sent Transport Format Combination Control messages for Tandem Free Operation. UPDATED:When RRC:TRANSPORT FORMAT COMBINATION CONTROL message is sent to a UE.

kpi_info.title: MEAS_REPORT_MSG_7A
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT messages including event 7A "The UE position changes more than an absolute threshold". UPDATED:When RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT message including event 7A is received from the UE."

kpi_info.title: MEAS_REPORT_MSG_7B
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT messages including event 7B "SFN-SFN measurement changes more than an absolute threshold". UPDATED:When RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT message including event 7B is received from the UE."

kpi_info.title: MEAS_REPORT_MSG_7C
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT messages including event 7C "GPS time and SFN time have drifted apart more than an absolute threshold". UPDATED:When RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT message including event 7C is received from the UE."

kpi_info.title: MEAS_REPORT_MSG_PER_REP
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT messages containing Periodical Reporting results. UPDATED:When RRC:MEASUREMENT REPORT message containing Periodical Reporting results is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_FACH_LOW_UTIL
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC state transitions from CELL_DCH state to CELL_FACH state due to low DCH utilisation. If downlink or uplink throughput in the number of bytes goes below the threshold defined with the RNC configuration parameters DCHutilRelThrDL or DCHutilRelThrUL, the PS DCH release procedure starts. This counter can be updated both for Rel99 DCH/DCH and HSDPA. For HSDPA calls the counter is updated if the final trigger to initiate state transition was uplink low utilization. But if the final trigger was HS-DSCH downlink low utilization, the counter is not updated even if before that also uplink low utilization indication would have been received from L2. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message after DCH to FACH state transition due to low DCH utilisation.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_DCH
kpi_info.use: Sum of operating time when UE is in CELL_DCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C89, gives the average operating time in CELL_DCH state. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from Cell_DCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that UE was in Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_DCH
kpi_info.use: Sum of squared operating time values when UE is in CELL_DCH state. Needed for variance calculation. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from Cell_DCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that UE was in Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_DCH
kpi_info.use: Denominator for counters M1006C87 and M1006C88, needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When duration value is updated to counters M1006C87 and M1006C88.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_FACH
kpi_info.use: Sum of operating time when UE is in CELL_FACH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C92, gives the average operating time in CELL_FACH state. The counter does not include those times that are used in CELL_FACH state when UE is performing Cell Update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e. UE is performing periodic Cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from Cell_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that UE was in Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_FACH
kpi_info.use: Sum of squared operating time values when UE is in CELL_FACH state. Needed for variance calculation. The counter does not include those times that are used in CELL_FACH state when UE is performing Cell Update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e. UE is performing periodic Cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from Cell_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that UE was in Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_FACH
kpi_info.use: Denominator for counters M1006C90 and M1006C91, needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When duration value is updated to counters M1006C90 and M1006C91.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_PCH
kpi_info.use: Sum of operating time when UE is in CELL_PCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C95, gives the average operating time in CELL_PCH state. Counting operating time in CELL_PCH is not interrupted if UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or cell reselection. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from CELL_PCH state to another state (excluding cell updates), this counter is updated by the duration that UE was in Cell_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_PCH
kpi_info.use: Sum of squared operating time values when UE is in CELL_PCH state. Needed for variance calculation. Counting operating time in CELL_PCH is not interrupted if UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or cell reselection. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from Cell_PCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that UE was in Cell_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_PCH
kpi_info.use: Denominator for counters M1006C93 and M1006C94, needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When duration value is updated to counters M1006C93 and M1006C94.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_URA_PCH
kpi_info.use: Sum of operating time when UE is in URA_PCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C98, gives the average operating time in URA_PCH state. Counting operating time in URA_PCH is not interrupted if UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or URA update. The unit of this counter is 10 seconds, meaning that value 1 means 10 seconds time in CELL-PCH state. Times shorter than 10 seconds will be counted as 10 seconds. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from URA_PCH state to another state (excluding cell updates), this counter is updated by the duration that UE was in URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_URA_PCH
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: This counter is never updated.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_URA_PCH
kpi_info.use: Denominator for counters M1006C96, needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When duration value is updated to counter M1006C96.

kpi_info.title: ASSISTANCE_DATA_DELIVERY_MSG
kpi_info.use: The number of sent UE positioning related Assistance Data Delivery messages. UPDATED:When RRC:ASSISTANCE DATA DELIVERY message is sent to a UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_SETUP_RETRANS_TRIG_BY_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of UE Triggered RRC Connection Setup retransmissions. RRC Connection Setup is retransmitted immediately and timer RRCconnRepTimer2 restarted if repeated RRC Connection Request is received during the ongoing RRC connection setup procedure. UPDATED:When RRC:RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message is received from the UE before timer RRCconnRepTimer2 expiry.

kpi_info.title: RRC_SETUP_RETRANS_TRIG_TIMER
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Setup retransmissions if RRC Connection Setup Complete is not received in time defined in RRCconnRepTimer2. UPDATED:When RRC Connection Setup retransmission is triggered by expiration of RRCconnRepTimer2.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_MSG
kpi_info.use: The total number of received RRC STATUS messages with Protocol Error Information. UPDATED:When RRC STATUS message is received with IE "Protocol error information" contents set to the value of the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_INFORMATION."

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_INVALID_PAGING2
kpi_info.use: The number of received RRC STATUS messages from the UE in case the UE receives a PAGING TYPE 2 message, which contains a protocol error causing the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_REJECT to be set to TRUE. UPDATED:When RRC STATUS message is received with the IE "Received message type" value PAGING TYPE 2 and the with IE "Protocol error information" set to the value of the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_INFORMATION."

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_INVALID_CONFIG
kpi_info.use: The number of received RRC STATUS messages from the UE in case radio access bearers for the CN domain indicated by the IE "CN domain identity" exist in the variable ESTABLISHED_RABS while signaling connection release is requested by CN. UPDATED:When RRC STATUS message is received with IE "Received message type" value SIGNALLING CONNECTION RELEASE and IE "Protocol error information" with value "Message not compatible with receiver state"

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_ASN1_VIOL_ENC_ERR
kpi_info.use: The number of received RRC STATUS messages from the UE in case the UE receives an RRC message on the DCCH for which the encoded message does not result in any valid abstract syntax value (or "encoding error"). UPDATED:When RRC STATUS message is received with the IE "Protocol error information" containing IE "Protocol error cause" set to value "ASN.1 violation or encoding error"."

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_ATT_DUE_NCCR
kpi_info.use: The number of cell update attempts due to Network Controlled Cell Reselection (NCCR) to another WCDMA carrier due to service reason. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC:CELL_UPDATE message from the UE after initiating NCCR to WCDMA due to service reason.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_SUCC_DUE_NCCR
kpi_info.use: The number of successful cell updates due to Network Controlled Cell Reselection (NCCR) to WCDMA due to service reason. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC:CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message to UE after network controlled cell reselection.

kpi_info.title: INTER_RAT_HO_UT_ATT_DUE_NCCR
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Inter-RAT cell change orders from UTRAN due to blind Network Controlled Cell Reselection (NCCR) to GPRS due to service reason. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC:CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REL_CCCH
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases on Common Control Channel. UPDATED:When RRC:RRC CONNECTION RELEASE message is sent to the UE on CCCH.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_MSLOST_URA_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to 'MS is lost' in URA_PCH state. UPDATED:When a UE in URA_PCH state does not respond to paging or does not make periodic URA update within URA_PCH supervision timer period and RNC releases the RRC Connection resources.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REL_RNC_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to RNC internal reason. UPDATED:When RLC unrecoverable error happens in CELL_DCH or CELL_FACH state with PS connection.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_MSLOST_CELL_FACH
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to 'MS is lost' in CELL_FACH state. UPDATED:When the RRC connection is released due to the expiration of CELL_FACH state supervision timer.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_HSDSCH_TO_FACH_LOW
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC state transitions from CELL DCH (HS-DSCH) state to CELL FACH state due to low utilisation, low throughput or inactivity. M1006C86 is updated along with this counter if the final trigger to initiate state transition was Rel99 uplink low utilization. UPDATED: When CELL_DCH (HS-DSCH) to CELL_FACH state transition occurs due to any other reason than radio interface failure.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_STATE_TO_CELL_PCH
kpi_info.use: Number of RRC state transitions from CELL DCH state to CELL_PCH state. UPDATED:The counter is updated when the UE is transferred from the Cell_DCH state to Cell_PCH state(after releasing of the CS-service or due to the inactivity detection of PS-RB(s)). The RRC entity will switch the MS directly from Cell_DCH to Cell/URA_PCH state

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_HSDSCH_TO_CELL_PCH
kpi_info.use: Number of RRC state transitions from CELL DCH (HS-DSCH) state to CELL_PCH state. UPDATED: The counter is updated in case of HSPDA if state transition occurs direct from Cell_DCH to Cell_PCH. Direct transition from HS-DSCH to Cell/URA_PCH can be used e.g. when there is a shortage of (DCH-pool) DMCU-resources. Also M1006C114 CELL DCH STATE TO CELL PCH is updated along with this counter.

kpi_info.title: DCH_REL_DUE_RES_TIMER
kpi_info.use: The number of times when PS NRT DCH is reconfigured to DCH 0/0 due to HSDPA resumption timer expiration. UPDATED:When PS NRT DCH is reconfigured to DCH 0/0 after HSDPA resumption timer expiration.

kpi_info.title: DCH_REL_DUE_RES_TIMER_REJECT
kpi_info.use: The number of times when HSDPA resumption timer has expired but reconfiguration to DCH 0/0 is rejected. The reason for rejection can be one of the following: 1) The maximum number of HSDPA users is exceeded in the cell. 2) It is not possible to allocate HSDPA power to the cell. 3) There is another parallel layer-3 procedure ongoing. 4) HdschGuardTimerHO or HsdschGuardTimerLowThroughput timer is running. UPDATED:When HSDPA resumption timer expires but layer 3 telecom entity or admission control rejects reconfiguration to DCH 0/0.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_SUCC_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful RRC connection re-establishments.Note: an RRC re-establisment is not done for RT in Nokia implementation When the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a CELL UPDATE procedure with cause "Radio link failure".

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_UE_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE replying with an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE. When the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the UE after a CELL UPDATE procedure with cause "Radio link failure".

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_NOREPLY_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE not replying to an RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM sent by RNC. When the RNC does not receive any reply to an RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM sent to the UE during a CELL UPDATE procedure initiated with cause "Radio link failure".

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_ATT
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted radio link additions with an active set update procedure. When an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message is sent by the serving RNC to the UE for adding one or more radio links to the active set. The counter is updated by the number of radio links that are attempted to add into the active set, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells tried to be added to the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_SUCC
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully added radio links with an active set update procedure. When the serving RNC receives an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links added with the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells which were added to the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_FAIL_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio link additions with an active set update procedure due to the UE responding with an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE FAILURE. When the serving RNC receives an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE FAILURE message from the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links that were attempted to add into the UE's active set with the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells which were tried to be added into the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_NOREPLY
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio link additions with an active set update procedure due to the UE not responding to an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE. When the serving RNC does not receive any reply to an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message sent to the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links that were attempted to add into the UE's active set with the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells which were tried to be added into the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_DEL_ATT
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted radio link deletions with an active set update procedure. When an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message is sent by the serving RNC to the UE for deleting one or more radio links to the active set. The counter is updated by the number of radio links that are attempted to delete from the active set, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells tried to be deleted from the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_DEL_SUCC
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully deleted radio links with an active set update procedure. When the serving RNC receives an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links deleted from the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure.The counter is updated for the cells which were deleted from the active set. In case of DRNC cell, object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: CELL_FACH_STATE_TO_HS_DSCH
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from CELL-FACH state to CELL-DCH state with HS-DSCH downlink transport channel. When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE after FACH to DCH transition and HS-DSCH downlink transport channel is allocated for the user.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_BLHO_UELOST_W_MEAS
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups to another frequency with blind handover method due to UE lost when handover was done to a cell indicated by target cell RSCP/EcNo measurement result. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP attempting to setup Radio Bearer on another frequency and the timer expires in the RNC and the attempt was done to a cell configured by the parameters and the attempt was done to a cell indicated by the UE inter-frequency RSCP or EcNo measurement result. The counter is also updated if the UE responds with RRC: CELL UPDATE

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The sum of operating time when the UE is in Enhanced Cell_FACH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C214, gives the average operating time in Enhanced Cell_FACH state. The counter does not include those times that are used in Enhanced Cell_FACH state when the UE ia performing cell update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e., the UE is performing the periodic cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED: When the RRC state is changed from Enhanced Cell_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that the UE was in Enhanced Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1006C213. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED: When the duration value is updated to counter M1006C213, this counter is updated by value 1.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (HSPA) to Enhanced Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the EFACH capable UE with condition that the channel switches from Cell_DCH state (on HSPA) to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_DCH_TO_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_DCH (HSPA) to Enhanced Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_DCH state (on HSPA) to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels)

kpi_info.title: ATT_EFACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HSPA). UPDATED: When a UL capacity request (RRC signalling entity initiated) or a DL capacity request (MAC-D entity initiated) is sent to RRM and the UE is in EFACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_EFACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HSPA). UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from EFACH state to Cell_DCH state (on HSPA)

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH to Enhanced Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When a dummy measurement report is got from the UE and RRM in the RNC is asked to change state for EFACH capable Rel8 UE from Cell_PCH state (on HSPA) to Cell_FACH (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_PCH_TO_EFACH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_PCH to Enhanced Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_PCH state (on HSPA) to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels)

kpi_info.title: ATT_EFACH_TO_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the EFACH capable Rel8 UE with condition that the channel switches from Cell_FACH state (on HSPA) to Cell_PCH state (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_EFACH_TO_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_FACH state (on HSPA) to Cell_PCH state (using HSPA transport channels)

kpi_info.title: CELL_FACH_TO_IDLE
kpi_info.use: "The number of state transitions from Cell_FACH to IDLE state. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC connection is released for any reason, either normally or due to some failure. Cell_FACH relocation or directed signalling connection re-establishment to another RNC shall not update this counter."

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (any transport channel). UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP message to the UE for transferring the UE to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_FACH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (any transport channel) to Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message to transfer the UE to Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message for transferring the UE to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. This does not include cases when the UE in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state makes Cell Update or URA Update and only temporarily visits in Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_FACH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH or URA_PCH to Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state and the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE triggering transfer to Cell_FACH. The counter is not be updated if the Cell Update or URA Update triggers RRC connection release or going back to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (any transport channel) to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state and state transition to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH is attempted with RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION.

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH or URA_PCH to Cell_DCH (any transport channel). UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state and the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE triggering direct transfer to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH_EDCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH). UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message for transferring the UE to Cell_DCH state with HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HS_DSCH_EDCH_TO_FACH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH) to Cell_FACH. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state with HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE, or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message for transferring the UE to Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH_EDCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH). UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message after a successful state transition from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH).

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_FLEXIBLE_RLC_UL
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use Flexible-RLC in uplink direction. M1006C202 can be updated in parallel with this counter because it indicates the Flexible-RLC usage in the downlink direction. UPDATED: When the UE replies with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful configuration of Flexible-RLC in uplink direction that was not in use before the reconfiguration."

kpi_info.title: ATT_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE is in URA_PCH/Cell_PCH/Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION to the UE, attempting to move the UE into Cell_DCH state under another BTS. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful inter-BTS layer change during transition to Cell_DCH state. The counter is updated for the target cell where the UE was successfully redirected.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of failed inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE but responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: CELL UPDATE or does not respond at all and a timer expires in the RNC. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: SIG_CONN_REL_IND_PS_END
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC: Signalling Connection Release Indication messages received from the UE with cause ""UE Requested PS Data session end"". Also M1006C58 is updated along with this counter. M1006C58 includes all Signalling Connection Release Indications with or without the cause IE. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: Signalling Connection Release Indication message from the UE, with value ""UE Requested PS Data session end"" in IE ""Signalling Connection Release Indication Cause""."

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_MIMO_SUCC
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use MIMO. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating successful MIMO allocation and MIMO was not active before the procedure.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_MIMO_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use MIMO. UPDATED: When the UE responds with negative RRC acknowledgement message, Cell Update or does not respond at all when trying to configure MIMO to use.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_64QAM_SUCC
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use 64QAM. When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating successful 64QAM allocation and 64QAM was not active before the procedure.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_64QAM_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use 64QAM. UPDATED: When the UE responds with negative RRC acknowledgement message, Cell Update or does not respond at all when trying to configure 64QAM to use.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_HSFACH_DL
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use HS-FACH downlink. UPDATED: When the RNC receives positive RRC protocol acknowledgement from the UE after configuring it to use HS-FACH downlink and HS-FACH was not in use before that.The counter is not updated in HS-RACH to HS-FACH reconfiguration."

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_HSFACH_UL
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use HS-FACH uplink (HS-RACH). UPDATED: When the RNC receives positive RRC protocol acknowledgement from the UE after configuring it to use HS-FACH uplink and HS-FACH uplink was not in use before that.The counter is updated also in HS-FACH (only DL) to HS-RACH (also UL) reconfiguration."

kpi_info.title: PAGING_DROP_LOW_PRIORITY
kpi_info.use: The number of low priority paging records that were dropped in L2 scheduling. UPDATED: When the L2 entity of RNC drops low priority paging message because of congestion.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_DROP_HIGH_PRIORITY
kpi_info.use: The number of high priority paging records that were dropped in L2 scheduling. UPDATED: When the L2 entity of RNC drops high priority paging message because of congestion.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_ATT_CS_CALL
kpi_info.use: "The number of started Cell Update procedures with establishment cause ""Originating Conversational Call"", ""Terminating Conversational Call"" or ""Emergency Call"".""Establishment cause"" is an optional IE in the Cell Update message introduced by 3GPP Rel5.Also one of basic Cell Update counters M1006C34-M1006C40 is updated along with this counter depending on the ""Cell update cause"" IE used by the UE.UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message with cause ""Originating Conversational Call"", ""Terminating Conversational Call"" or ""Emergency Call""."

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_SUCC_CS_CALL
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful Cell Update procedures with establishment cause ""Originating Conversational Call"", ""Terminating Conversational Call"" or ""Emergency Call"". ""Establishment cause"" is an optional IE in the Cell Update message introduced by 3GPP Rel5.Also one of basic Cell Update counters M1006C34-M1006C40 is updated along with this counter depending on the ""Cell update cause"" IE used by the UE.UPDATED: When the UE responds Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete or UTRAN Mobility Information Confirm after the RNC has sent Cell Update Confirm as a response to Cell Update with the mentioned causes."

kpi_info.title: UE_ID_LFDPHONE_STATE_TR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a UE is identified as Legacy Fast Dormancy Phone based on state transition behaviour. UPDATED: When the RNC identifies a UE as Legacy Fast Dormancy UE based on its state transition behaviour and therefore IMSI is stored for later use. The counter is updated only once per RRC connection. Here "state transition behaviour" means that the UE has sent Signalling Connection Release Indication, the RNC has commanded the UE to PCH state, but instead the UE went to idle state.

kpi_info.title: LFDPHONE_TO_PCH
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a UE identified as Legacy Fast Dormancy Phone has been successfully transferred to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. Also other state transition counters for example M1006C47, M1006C49 or M1006C114 are updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives Physical Channel Reconfiguration complete indicating successful transition to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state from a UE that has been identified as LFDphone.

kpi_info.title: LFDPHONE_PCH_TO_FACH_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of times when Legacy Fast Dormancy Phone has made PCH->FACH or PCH->DCH transition. Also other state transition counters for example M1006C171 are updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives positive RRC protocol ack message indicating successful PCH->FACH or PCH->DCH transition for LFDphone. Here "PCH" means either Cell_PCH or URA_PCH.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HIGH_PEAK_REDIR_MCRNC
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection requests handled by IPA-RNC that were successfully redirected to co-siting mcRNC because of UE support for high peak rate. UPDATED: When the IPA-RNC successfully redirects an incoming RRC connection to mcRNC because of UE support for high peak rate.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_LOW_PEAK_REDIR_MCRNC
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection requests handled by IPA-RNC that were received from low peak rate capable UEs and redirected to co-siting mcRNC because of load balancing. UPDATED: When the IPA-RNC successfully redirects an incoming RRC connection to IPA-RNC even if the UE is not high peak rate capable. This happens because of load balancing reason.

kpi_info.title: HIGH_PEAK_UE_TO_IPARNC
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection requests handled by IPA-RNC that were received from high peak rate capable UEs and assigned to IPA-RNC because of load balancing. UPDATED: When the IPA-RNC receives RRC Connection Request from high peak rate capable UE but it is not redirected to mcRNC because of load balancing reasons.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_REDIR_MCRNC
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection requests handled by IPA-RNC for which redirection to co-siting mcRNC failed. UPDATED: When redirecting an RRC connection to mcRNC fails.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_INACT
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of inactivity or PS RAB release. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of Cell_DCH to Cell_FACH/Cell_PCH/URA_PCH transition or Iu release. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_CH_SWI
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of switch from HSPA to Rel99 DCH transport channels. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of HS-DSCH to Rel99 DCH (DCH x/y) channel type switch. HS-DSCH switches directly to Rel99 DCH without any bit rate (DCH 0/0) are not included in this counter. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC.

kpi_info.title: LTE_REDIR_PREV_TIMER
kpi_info.use: The number of times when Smart LTE Layering is prevented by timer RNMOBI->SmartLTELayeringPrevT. High value in this counter may indicate insufficient coverage of the target LTE layer, or incorrect neighbour cell definition. UPDATED: When Smart LTE Layering would trigger RRC Connection Release, but it is prevented by timer RNMOBI->SmartLTELayeringPreventionT.

kpi_info.title: ATT_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted intra-BTS inter-frequency PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transitions with MBLB enabled. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When the UE is in URA_PCH/Cell_PCH/Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: Cell Update Confirm or RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration to the UE, attempting to move the UE into Cell_DCH state under the same BTS but different frequency and MBLB functionality is enabled.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful intra-BTS PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH state transitions where frequency layer was changed because of MBLB. The counter is updated for the target cell where the UE was successfully redirected. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete indicating a successful intra-BTS inter-frequency layer change during transition to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of failed intra-BTS frequency layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition with MBLB enabled. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete, sends RRC: Cell Update to the original frequency or a timer waiting for UE response expires in the RNC, after a frequency layer change was attempted.

kpi_info.title: CANC_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of intra-BTS frequency layer changes in PCH to Cell_DCH transition cancelled because of CPICH RSCP quality check. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When inter-frequency PCH to Cell_DCH is cancelled because of CPICH RSCP value sent by the UE in RRC: Cell Update does not fulfill the quality check criteria.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_WCDMA_REDIR
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases with redirection information to another WCDMA frequency. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE including redirection information to another WCDMA frequency. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC.

kpi_info.title: CS_CALL_TERM_RE_EST
kpi_info.use: The number of CS voice calls terminated during RRC connection re-establishment procedure. This counter can be used to analyze the cases where the user terminates the call because it becomes mute for a while during re-establishment, and thus the user experiences a drop even if the call could recover soon after that. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND or RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST requesting to release CS RAB while the RNC is waiting for RRC connection re-establishment to happen.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_CS_REL
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases with LTE redirection information because of CS Voice Call release. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by LTE redirection because of CS voice call release.

kpi_info.title: ATT_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA. Includes initial DB-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DB-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. M1006C209 is also updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION to the UE with information to configure the radio bearer to use DB-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA. It includes initial DB-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DB-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. M1006C210 is also updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE after a successful configuration of Radio Bearer to use DB-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA_NOREP
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA because of UE not responding. Also M1006C211 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message sent by the RNC for DB-HSDPA establishment and a timer expires in the RNC.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA because of UE responding with a failure message. Also M1006C212 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE for DB-HSDPA establishment attempt.

kpi_info.title: DCH_STATE_ALLOC_PTT_SUCC
kpi_info.use: The number of successful PTT call attempts in the cell. UPDATED:When PTT RAB is successfully transitioned to CELL_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: DCH_STATE_ALLOC_PTT_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of failed PTT call attempts in the cell. UPDATED:When CELL_DCH state allocation for PTT RAB is not possible due to RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration failure/ a second RRC: Cell update message is received from the UE in same cell/ no response from PTT UE to RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration.

kpi_info.title: ACT_OPER_TM_PTT_UE
kpi_info.use: Sum of PTT UE operating time in active state. This counter divided by the denominator M1006C300 gives the average time that PTT RAB is in active state with user plane allocated. UPDATED:When PTT RAB leaves active state, duration for which PTT RAB was active(time between Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete to PTT dormancy timer expiry) is updated to this counter

kpi_info.title: DENOM_ACT_OPER_TM_PTT_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of samples for active state operating time counter M1006C299. UPDATED:Incremented by one every time SUM OF PTT UE ACTIVE STATE OPERATING TIMES is updated

kpi_info.title: MEH_INCR_TVM_PEND_TIME
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the RNC configures increased Traffic Volume Measurement pending time for the UE due to high cell load detected by Mass Event Handler functionality. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the RNC sends RRC: MEASUREMENT CONTROL to the UE with an increased Traffic Volume Pending time due to high cell load.

kpi_info.title: MEH_INCR_CQI_CYCLE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocations where increased CQI feedback cycle is configured for the UE due to high cell load detected by Mass Event Handler functionality. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the first HS-DSCH flow is allocated for the UE in a cell. This can be initial allocation during RAB setup, state transition to Cell_DCH, user plane setup from DCH 0/0, serving cell change, channel type switch or HHO.
